                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12374675" author="hossman" created="Sun, 16 Apr 2006 15:40:50 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;patch includes a static initConfig method in SolrConfig so that tests can re-init the config using whatever fiel they want.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(I don&apos;t consider this a perfect solution, but it&apos;s the simplest one given that SolrConfig is a singleton &amp;#8211; trying to change that would be scary)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;patch also includes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;changes to TestHarness, AbstractSolrTestCase, and all of the existing test class to utilize this&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;new copies of the configs previously used from the apps/SolrTest directory&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;build.xml change so the CWD for the junit tests is a new test-files directory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;with this patch, all conections between the junit tests and the legacy SolrTest code/directory are severed.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;if no one objects, i&apos;ll commit this in a day or two.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12374969" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Wed, 19 Apr 2006 01:20:26 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It should only be used for testing though... (it&apos;s not thread-safe, among other issues having to do with how it&apos;s used...)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12374973" author="hossman" created="Wed, 19 Apr 2006 01:44:15 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; It should only be used for testing though&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;agreed, I was going to add a big fat warning about that, but I figured it would be obvious since the Config object is a singleton ... but i&apos;ll add it anyway.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12375046" author="hossman" created="Wed, 19 Apr 2006 14:01:27 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;patch commited with added warning about initConfig&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
